reviews.text:
Always like the razor clams here. It is surprising to find razor clam tastes so good in different cooking style here. Worth to try. 
The braised bean curd with Chinese cabbage is one of my favourites. Seafood (including razor clam) is used in the soup. It is definitely not veggie as it sounds.
The food is really really good!   We have to wait for 15 min to get a  table.  But the wait is worthy.  It's slightly different from traditional Cantonese style.   👍👍👍

Chain restaurant with creative dishes using seasonal ingredients. I love that they change their menu constantly. The dishes were well made and reasonably priced. It's quite popular so do expect a queue during peak hours.

Special Singapore cuisine that you couldn't normally find. A worldwide chain restaurant of quality food. Pretty spacious and friendly staff. Interesting they offer birthday celebrations arrangement where they will prepare birthday song and a toy as gift as they take out the cake prepared by customer. I listened thrice on the same night! A good place for family with elderly and kids.
so far so good, however quality is not very stable very well
